'\"! tbl | mmdoc
'\"macro stdmacro
.TH SMTGC 1M
.SH NAME
smtgc \- display or terminate SMT frame service
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B /usr/etc/smtgc
[
.BI \-f " type"
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Smtgc
may be used to force
.I smtd
to terminate SMT frame services to some Management Agent
Program(
.I MAP
) by closing sockets that are used as communication channel
between MAP(s) and
.IR smtd .
It may also be used as a ``garbage collecting'' tool for unused but
opened sockets.
If
.I smtgc
is invoked without options, a list of sockets will be
printed out with each line showing the service frame type and socket number.
The
.BI \-f " type"
option causes
.I smtgc
to terminate
.I type
frame service.
.I Type
is a mnemonic name or its numeric value from the following list:
.sp
.RS
.TS
l l l
l n l.
Name	Value	Description
all		all services
NIF	1	Neighbor Information Frame
CSIF	2	Configuration Station Info Frame
OSIF	3	Operation Station Info Frome
ECF	4	Echo Frame
RAF	5	Resource Allocation Frame
RDF	6	Request Denied Frame
SRF	7	Status Report Frame
GET_PMF	8	Get Parameter Management Frame
CHG_PMF	9	Change Parameter Management Frame
ADD_PMF	10	Add Parameter Management Frame
RM_PMF	11	Remove Parameter Management Frame
ESF	255	Extended Service Frame
.TE
.RE
.P
Only the super-user may remove SMT frame service(s).
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
If
.I smtgc
fails for any reason,
it prints an appropriate message on standard error and exits with a
non-zero status.
.SH SEE ALSO
smtd(1M)
